  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee on Banking Supervision guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (UK)\n- Anti-Money Laundering laws in many countries\n\n3. Key Regulatory Measures:\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Mandatory transaction reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Asset freezing and seizure provisions\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Compliance Requirements:\n- Financial institutions must implement robust anti-money laundering programs\n- Regular audits and monitoring of financial transactions\n- Training for employees on identifying suspicious activities\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
